2004-06-01  Philippe Thibault  <thibaup@iro.umontreal.ca>

	* lib/AtomSet.cc, lib/AtomSet.h: New filter for Phosphate atom group.

	* lib/Residue.cc: setTheoretical() now adds hydrogens and lone pairs

	* lib/AtomTypeStore.h, lib/AtomType.h, lib/AtomType.cc:
	- Phosphate atom group type is now known as Phosphorous, for P
	atom.
	- New Phosphate atom group: { P, O1P, O2P, O3P, O3', O5' } (stays
	also in Backbone atom group)

2004-06-01  Philippe Thibault  <thibaup@iro.umontreal.ca>

	* lib/AtomTypeStore.h, lib/AtomType.h, lib/AtomType.cc:
	- Phosphate atom group type is now known as Phosphorous, for P
	atom.
	- New Phosphate atom group: { P, O1P, O2P, O3P, O3', O5' } (stays
	also in Backbone atom group)

2004-05-27  Philippe Thibault  <thibaup@iro.umontreal.ca>

	* lib/RiboseBuilder.cc, lib/Relation.cc: - updated to residue class
	modifications

	* Relation.cc: - updated to residue class modifications

	* lib/Model.cc: - new method to add hydrogens and lone pairs to each
	residue.

	* lib/Residue.h, lib/Residue.cc, lib/ExtendedResidue.h, lib/ExtendedResidue.cc:
	- Residue::iterator::setLocal(): new iterator method to adjust
	pointed atom's local coordinates.
	- Residue::finalize():           doesn't adds hydrogens and lone
	pairs anymore.
	- Residue::addHydrogens():       doesn't adds HO3' anymore -> in a
	separate method ( addHO3p() ).
	- Residue::setIdeal():           renamed to setTheoretical(), now
	has an optional backbone addition.
	- Residue::get{Pucker,Glycosyl}Type(): now returns an unknown
	property type in the case of a failure (not nucleic acid ...)

